<title type="html"><![CDATA[Preventing HMTL5 &lt;video&gt; from automatically downloadin]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="https://forums.whatwg.org/bb3/viewtopic.php?t=4129&amp;p=5185#p5185"><![CDATA[
If you don't use the autobuffer or autoplay attributes, then HTML5 allows the browser to only download enough data to show the first frame, and then suspend the download until the user plays.<br /><br />If you use a poster=&quot;&quot; image then HTML5 allows the browser to just download the image and wait with downloading any video data until the user plays.<br /><br />If the browser you're using is not suspending the download, then you should complain to the browser vendor. (I think at least Firefox 3.5 suspends the download.)<br /><br />If you don't want to wait until browsers have fixed this, you can work around it by using an &lt;img&gt; and swap it for a &lt;video&gt; with script when the user clicks on the image, or similar.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="https://forums.whatwg.org/bb3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=4">zcorpan</a> — Thu Sep 17, 2009 7:38 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
